The paper deals with interference analysis in a cellular system with massive MIMO, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of stochastic geometry to model the spatial distribution of users suggests that the paper may also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The analysis of the statistical distributions of interferences experienced by a typical uplink is related to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as it deals with the handling of multiuser interference. Finally, the use of MRC and ZF receivers suggests that the paper may also fall under the computer communications (cs.COM) sub-category, as it deals with the design and analysis of communication protocols.
